  "verdict": "The EC-Maass difference in M4/M2^2 is statistically significant (z=-33.4, p=0.00e+00) but the effect size is small (Cohen's d=-0.34). EC sits 0.4% below Catalan; Maass sits 1.2% above. MF dim-1 is closest at 0.3% below. All three SU(2) families converge to the same Catalan chain, with finite-sample deviations that differ in sign and magnitude due to arithmetic vs spectral convergence. The moment hierarchy U(1) < SU(2) < USp(4) is definitively confirmed."
